    <thetext>Section 5.2 says:
    The notation “x modulo y” (y must be finite and nonzero)
    computes a value k of the same sign as y (or zero) such that
    abs(k) &lt; abs(y) and x-k = q * y for some integer q.

You could make the definition a bit simpler by requiring that y be a positive integer, which is true of all uses of &apos;modulo&apos; in the spec.</thetext>
